    {
        "url": "/quotes/molly_antopol_728508",
        "quote": "One of the things I admire about longer stories is the way writers can work with dead time and slower, more idle moments - not only can they feel expansive, they feel lived-in; the unhurried pacing often makes the endings even more resonant and surprising for me.",
